Data structure: keep CSV as-is. Semicolons are fine — DataTables child rows parse them client-side. No JSON, no extra rows.

The accordion pattern uses DataTables row.child() API — built-in, no extra library. The expand toggle lives inside the theme_name cell render:


[ ▶  Replace 'Adobe Reader' with...  ][ description... ]
   ↓ click
[ ▼  Replace 'Adobe Reader' with...  ][ description... ]
     • https://helpx.adobe.com/...
     • https://helpx.adobe.com/...
affected_pages stays hidden (visible: false) but searchable. The child row renders URLs as a <ul> on expand.

One small datatables.js fix needed first. Line 1294 does Object.assign(dataTableOptions, rest) which overwrites the internal columnDefs array if you pass your own. It should concat instead:

Read datatables.js (lines 1289-1300)
Edit datatables.js
Added 3 lines
Now the themes fragmentConfig can pass columnDefs and initComplete without blowing away internal defs. Here's what the themes config will look like (for when you wire it up):


var themesFragmentConfig = {
    tableSelector: '#tab5-fragment #tab5-table',
    statusSelector: '#tab5-fragment #tab5-status',
    checkBoxes: false,
    printPDF: false, exportExcel: false, emailButton: false, jiraButton: false,
    colVis: true,
    dataTableOptions: {
        columnDefs: [
            {
                targets: 3,          // affected_pages — hide but keep searchable
                visible: false,
                searchable: true
            },
            {
                targets: 1,          // theme_name — prepend toggle arrow
                render: function (data, type) {
                    if (type !== 'display') return data;
                    return '<span class="themes-row-toggle" title="Show affected pages" '
                         + 'style="cursor:pointer;user-select:none;margin-right:6px;">▶</span>'
                         + data;
                }
            }
        ],
        initComplete: function (settings) {
            var api = new jQuery.fn.dataTable.Api(settings);
            jQuery(api.table().body()).on('click', '.themes-row-toggle', function () {
                var row = api.row(jQuery(this).closest('tr'));
                var toggle = jQuery(this);
                if (row.child.isShown()) {
                    row.child.hide();
                    toggle.text('▶');
                } else {
                    var pages = row.data()[3] || '';   // affected_pages col
                    var urls = pages.split(';').map(function(u){ return u.trim(); }).filter(Boolean);
                    var html = '<ul class="themes-pages-list" style="margin:4px 0 4px 2em;padding:0">'
                        + urls.map(function(u){
                            return '<li><a href="' + u + '" target="_blank">' + u + '</a></li>';
                          }).join('')
                        + '</ul>';
                    row.child(html).show();
                    toggle.text('▼');
                }
            });
        }
    }
};